<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684766>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 5. Frequency distribution of the size of the red subterminal band (width of red spot in cell M3) on the underside of the right hindwing of female Delias aestiva aestiva based on a sample (n = 35, MFBC) of specimens from Darwin,Northern Territory.Sample mean and standard deviation are indicated above graph. The grey bar indicates the size of the corresponding band in the two female specimens of D. aestiva smithersi examined." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4684766/files/figure.png" .

